                <section class="faq-section">
                    <h2>Common Questions About Long-Distance Moving</h2>

                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <span>What is considered a long-distance move?</span>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <div class="faq-answer-content">
                                A long-distance move typically involves relocating over 100 miles or across state lines.
                                These moves fall under interstate regulations, and may have different pricing and
                                logistics than local moves within the same city.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <span>Are my belongings insured during a long-distance move?</span>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <div class="faq-answer-content">
                                Your belongings are insured during a long-distance move, with federal law requiring
                                companies to offer basic liability coverage. Customers can also upgrade their protection
                                to include more substantial coverage by purchasing a full replacement insurance plan.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <span>Can I include temporary storage with a long-distance move?</span>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <div class="faq-answer-content">
                                It's possible to include temporary storage with a long-distance move, whether you want
                                to store a few items or a large collection of belongings. Storage could be for a few
                                days as you wait to move in, or for weeks or months when you need additional time.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <span>How far in advance should I book my long-distance move?</span>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <div class="faq-answer-content">
                                We recommend booking your long-distance move at least 4-6 weeks in advance, especially
                                during peak moving season (May-September). However, we understand that sometimes moves
                                happen quickly, and we'll do our best to accommodate last-minute requests whenever
                                possible.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
